cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "overleaf-sync-now: instant Overleaf-to-Dropbox sync for AI coding agents"
authors:
  - family-names: Han
    given-names: Lu
    website: "https://luhan.io/"
abstract: >
  A command-line tool and AI-agent skill that triggers Overleaf's hidden
  POST /project/{id}/dropbox/sync-now endpoint on demand, so AI coding agents
  (Claude Code, OpenAI Codex CLI) always edit the latest version of a LaTeX
  paper instead of a stale local Dropbox copy lagging 10–20 minutes behind
  Overleaf's polling-based sync. Includes a PreToolUse hook for Claude Code
  and a Playwright-managed browser login flow that works around Chrome 130+
  App-Bound Encryption.
keywords:
  - overleaf
  - latex
  - dropbox
  - sync
  - claude-code
  - codex
  - ai-tools
  - agent-skill
  - mcp
  - academic-writing
  - paper-writing
  - scientific-writing
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/hanlulong/overleaf-sync-now"
url: "https://github.com/hanlulong/overleaf-sync-now"
